cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on representing robot experiences in an episodic-like memory for action execution. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes an unsupervised deep episodic memory model for encoding, recalling, and predicting action experiences. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the model predicts future frames, which involves image processing. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes a deep neural network architecture for representing experiences. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper evaluates the generalization capability of the proposed model in a real-world scenario on a humanoid robot.
